Business Requirement

Your company is launching an e-commerce application.

The application must be highly available across 2 Availability Zones.

The architecture consists of:

A public-facing Application Load Balancer (ALB)
A web tier
An application tier
A MySQL database

Infrastructure Requirements
Networking
One VPC
Two Public Subnets
Two Private App Subnets
Two Private DB Subnets
One Internet Gateway
One NAT Gateway
Route tables with the appropriate associations

Web Tier
Two EC2 instances
One EC2 in each public subnet
Both should receive traffic from the ALB
Application Tier
Two EC2 instances
One EC2 in each private app subnet
The web tier should communicate with the app tier

Database Tier
One MySQL RDS instance
It should be deployed in the private DB subnets
Only the application tier should be able to connect to it

Security
Web Security Group
App Security Group
Database Security Group
Load Balancer
One Application Load Balancer
One Target Group
One Listener
Register only the web servers with the Target Group
Business Constraints
Infrastructure should be easy to scale.
The design should follow Terraform best practices.
Avoid unnecessary duplication.
Future expansion to 4 or 6 web servers should require minimal code changes.